==English==
===Etymology===
From French ''[[archives]]'', from Latin ''[[archīva]]'', from Greek ''[[arkheia]]'', plural of ''[[arkheion]]'', "town hall".

===Pronunciation===
* ''[[RP]]:''
** {{IPA|/ˈɑːkaɪv/}}
** {{AHD|är'kīv'}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# A place for [[store|storing]] earlier, and often [[historical]], material.  An archive usually contains [[document]]s ([[letter]]s, [[record]]s, [[newspaper]]s, etc.) or other types of [[media]] kept for historical interest.

